oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Shaving kit of Cpl. Robert Brownlow Wilson
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This Gilette Khaki Set shaving kit with razor and blades belonged to Cpl. Robert Brownlow Wilson of Cades Cove. He served in Co. B, 117th Inf. Regt. in France during World War I. He was gassed and survived the war. After the war, he returned to his life as a farmer in Blount County and lived to age 95.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
